@page
@{
	Layout = "_Layout";
    ViewData["Title"] = "The National Tutoring Programme";
}

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">The National Tutoring Programme</h1>
        <p class="govuk-body">The National Tutoring Programme gives state-funded schools additional funding to help young people who have had their education disrupted by coronavirus (COVID-19).</p>
	    <p class="govuk-body">Schools can choose high-quality subsidised tutoring from 3 routes:</p>
	    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
		    <li>
			    <a asp-fragment="find-a-tuition-partner" class="govuk-link">Find a Tuition Partner</a>
		    </li>
		    <li>
			    <a asp-fragment="academic-mentors" class="govuk-link">Academic Mentors</a>
		    </li>
		    <li>
			    <a asp-fragment="school-led-tutoring" class="govuk-link">School-Led Tutoring</a>
		    </li>
	    </ul>
	    <a asp-page="/Options" role="button" draggable="false" class="govuk-button govuk-button--start" data-module="govuk-button" data-testid="call-to-action">
		    Start now
		    <svg class="govuk-button__start-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="17.5" height="19" viewBox="0 0 33 40" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
			    <path fill="currentColor" d="M0 0h13l20 20-20 20H0l20-20z" />
		    </svg>
	    </a>
        
	    <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Before you start</h2>
	    <p class="govuk-body">You must:</p>
	    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
		    <li>
			    be a state-funded school or academy
		    </li>
		    <li>
			    know your school’s postcode
		    </li>
	    </ul>
		
	    <h2 id="find-a-tuition-partner" class="govuk-heading-m">Find a Tuition Partner</h2>
	    <p class="govuk-body">Schools can access the full list of quality assured tuition partners through the ‘Find a Tuition Partner’ service. The tuition partners offer a wide range of subjects and options for how to deliver tutoring to schools.</p>
	    <p class="govuk-body">The cost of tuition partners is 60% subsidised.</p>
		
	    <h2 id="academic-mentors" class="govuk-heading-m">Academic Mentors</h2>
	    <p class="govuk-body">Academic mentors are an ‘in class’ resource to work alongside teachers to help with a range of interventions. Academic mentors are typically employed to work in 15 hour blocks of support to provide intensive support where needed.</p>
	    <p class="govuk-body">The cost of academic mentors is 60% subsidised.</p>
		
	    <h2 id="school-led-tutoring" class="govuk-heading-m">School-Led Tutoring</h2>
	    <p class="govuk-body">School-Led Tutoring lets schools use existing staff or external tutoring resources they trust to deliver tutoring to their pupils. This route offers flexibility for schools to identify their own tutors.</p>
	    <p class="govuk-body">School-Led Tutoring’s funding is based on the number of pupil premium students.</p>
	    <p class="govuk-body">The cost of School-Led Tutoring is 60% subsidised.</p>
    </div>

	<div class="govuk-grid-column-one-third">
		<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Related content</h2>
		<p class="govuk-body"><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-tutoring-programme-ntp" class="govuk-link">National Tutoring Programme guidance</a></p>
	</div>
</div>
